post_text: PLEASE SHARE WITH AN AVONDALE HIGH SCHOOL STUDENT THAT YOU KNOW: Are you a high school student considering a future in the health-related or medical fields? If so, consider joining Avondale’s second-year HOSA (Health Occupations Students of America) Chapter! Members have the opportunity to gain essential knowledge and skills within the healthcare industry by competing in a chosen individual or team event. We gradually prepare for our annual conference in December in the hopes of qualifying for further rounds! Our first online meeting of the year will be on Thursday, September 17th at 1:30 PM. All students are welcome, so please consider joining us! Please email Ms. Beels at alexandra.beels@avondaleschools.org for more information or if you have any questions!

text:
HUGE SHOUT OUT to Avondale High School Art Department for setting up a Donors Choose Fundraiser and to ALL of the folks who supported it! The request "Ceramic Tool Kits" was fully funded so that every AHS 3D Design and Ceramics student can borrow an individual tool kit during remote learning and when we return to in-class instruction, they won't have to share. With these tool kits, students can have an authentic learning experience in art, even if it has to be from home! Way to go Mrs. Palombit for heading this up!

THANK YOU to every community member, family member, friend, and stranger who helped fund this project.

post_text:
The Avondale Theatre Company kicks of the 2020-21 season with "Censored on Final Appoach"! It is the true story of the Women Air Service Pilots (W.A.S.P.'s) who served their country during WWII - a story of resilience! The performances will be streamed on November 6 and 7, 2020 at 7:05pm. Stay tuned for the cast and crew announcement!

Shout out to Avondale Theater Director, Mr. Mike Sheldon who has devised a rehearsal schedule that allows the students to have a theater experience this fall. The students will be assigned different rehearsal and work schedules so they can be broken into smaller groups. There will never be more than 9 students in any rehearsal room and, they will be doing temperature checks and wearing masks at all times.

Please share: Parents wishing to enroll their student(s) in our Blessings in a Backpack program, please fill out the form at this link:
https://forms.gle/PdsACS8KPo7tWKtf9. Blessings in a Backpack provides simple meals at NO COST each week during the school year for families who need assistance. While Avondale Schools is conducting remote learning, meals will be disbursed in conjunction with the Chartwells Food Service Breakfast and Lunch distributions. (Watch for details about distribution dates, times, and locations.) Sign up today!

link:
AVONDALE HIGH SCHOOL PARENTS:

Avondale Esports IS coming back! Even though Avondale High School is currently closed due to the pandemic, some clubs are continuing online. IF your student likes to play video games and wants to take their skills to a competitive level, then this is the club for them!

Two information meetings TODAY! The first from 3pm to 4pm and the second from 5pm to 6pm. If you or your student is unable to attend the online meeting, you can request an information packet in the forum which will be sent to you.

To receive the link for the meeting you must sign up using the google forum link below. Please use your first and last name to enter the zoom room.
Sign Up Sheet: https://forms.gle/T2Mx8HFanAYdVnbJ7

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS Doug Wilson! A leader wearing many hats during his tenure at Avondale High School, Mr. Wilson is announced as the new Avondale High School Principal. Mr. Wilson attended Grand Valley State University where he received his Bachelor’s Degree in Biology and his Master’s Degree in Education. He also received a certificate from ASCD for Curriculum and an Administrative Certificate from Grand Valley State. Mr. Wilson participated in and led many district and high school initiatives while serving as Assistant Principal of Avondale High School for five years. He was instrumental on the High School Visioning Committee, was a FAME (Formative Assessment) Coach, leads the Avondale IMPACT program, chaired the District Technology Committee, served on bargaining unit committees, was the school point-person for bond projects, was the lead administrator for our transition to NGSS Science, created the district’s Curriculum Think Tank and MORE!

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS Maryanne Munroe, new Assistant Superintendent for Student Services! Mrs. Munroe brings expertise and commitment to her new role as Assistant Superintendent for Student Services. The top candidate during the District’s search to lead the department, Mrs. Munroe earned her Bachelor of Science in Special Education from University of Detroit Mercy; her Master of Arts in Educational Leadership from Saginaw Valley State University; and Continuing Education Credits with a Concentration in Doctoral Studies in Educational Leadership from Walden University. She holds certifications in Special Education, K-12 Administration, K-12 Central Office Enhancement, K-12 Emotionally Impaired (SE) and Grades 7-12 History (CC). A Fullbright Hayes Fellow and a Gerstacker Fellow, Mrs. Munroe was most recently the Principal of Avondale Middle School. Prior to that she was the Director of International Programs and Special Education as well as a Teacher Consultant and Assistant Principal in the Oxford School District. Congratulations again!

post_text: SHOUT OUT to our Avondale Busy Bee and Early Learning Center staff!! Busy Bee and Early Learning staff are planning to utilize a 700 student building to accommodate a LIMITED number of students for day care in the fall. This is a realistic solution for parents who must return to work in the fall. Strict protocols can be more easily enforced than an environment of 400 students in a 400 student building, 700 students in a 700 student building or 1000 students in a 1000 building. Thank you to the Busy Bee and Early Learning staff and Avondale administrators who put this program together to help our families.

post_text:
Information for parents and students of the Class of 2020 ...

This week, parents and student of the Class of 2020 received a letter from the AHS principal regarding a change of plans for Prom. As the planned venue is no longer an option for holding Prom, Principal Hyde is working to move the Prom to AHS. She will be meeting with student leaders to discuss and has asked for parents interested in helping to email Annette.mcavoy@avondaleschools.org to express their interest in helping. Please do so if you are interested and available to assist.

In addition, Mrs. Hyde mentioned that parents should be prepared in the event that the Commencement Ceremony planned for July 27th has to be cancelled…
text:
Information for parents and students of the Class of 2020 ...

This week, parents and student of the Class of 2020 received a letter from the AHS principal regarding a change of plans for Prom. As the planned venue is no longer an option for holding Prom, Principal Hyde is working to move the Prom to AHS. She will be meeting with student leaders to discuss and has asked for parents interested in helping to email Annette.mcavoy@avondaleschools.org to express their interest in helping. Please do so if you are interested and available to assist.

In addition, Mrs. Hyde mentioned that parents should be prepared in the event that the Commencement Ceremony planned for July 27th has to be cancelled…

post_text: The Avondale RoboJackets robotics team is looking for new members for the 2020-21 school year! All students entering 6th - 12th are encouraged to apply. If you know of a student who wants to chase exellence as a memeber of a highly-effective team check out this opportunity! Team members experience the most exciting aspects of engineering and develop skills in design, fabrication, and programming by working along side professionals. Learn more: http://www.team3538.com/members/rj-application/

THIS SOUNDS FUN!! Please join us! Students in middle and high school are invited to enjoy a fun and supportive presentation on June 9th. The Rochester Auburn Hills Community Coalition is supporting us by providing a Virtual Youth Dialogue Day titled "The Magic of Hope" Join us to learn about the magical power of routines, the importance of unplugging and how to let go of what you can't control.

This one hour presentation by magician and motivational speaker, Anthony Crupido is sure to help us end the year with smiles and support.

This event takes place from 11:00am - 12:00pm on Tuesday, June 9th.

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School senior Azaria Moody! From Mrs. Cramer: "Azaria - in four years you never once behaved as if you were having a bad day. You kept me laughing with your sly humor, and your good nature shone each time I saw you. You are a genuine, funny, bright girl who deserves every single good thing coming your way, and I can’t wait to watch it happen!!" Congratulations again Azaria!

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School senior Devin Sawyer! From Ms. Olszak: "Devin, you have overcome many obstacles to get here and have faced each and everyone of them head on which will serve you well in your endeavors after high school. post_text: CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School senior Ariana Badgero! From Ms. Chrisman: "Ariana, you were somewhat leary from the start about taking AP Biology this year. However, I am so very pleased that you decided to stick it out. You were definitely one of the most quiet students I had in class this year, but that does not discount your brilliance. I witnessed your constant efforts to engage with and understand the concepts behind that which we were doing on a daily basis. Your almost secret sense of strong self motivation is a piece of your character that will serve you well in the future. I am proud of you, as you should be proud of yourself. I wish you the best, I know you will do great things, I hope you ensure that they bring you joy as you do so." Ariana will be attending Oakland Community College this fall to study Health Science. Congratulations again Ariana!

post_text: Graduates from the Class of 2020 are invited to join in a car parade on Thursday, May 28. Graduates will meet and line up in their cars in the AHS parking lot at 6:30 PM. Please feel free to decorate your car and wear your cap and gown. The parade will begin promptly at 7:00 PM and follow the route highlighted on the map provided. Family and friends are encouraged to cheer on the graduates along the parade route. Please adhere to all CDC guidelines pertaining to social distancing and only park and stand on public property. Graduates must also adhere to all CDC guidelines and traffic laws. Graduates will be asked to remain in their cars. Please make sure your car is tastefully decorated. Profanity, vulgar music, and drugs/alcohol will not be tolerated. This is a parent sponsored event. Please contact Jen Donaghy (248-561-7656),Jen Richter (248-396-7427), or Jen Rosasco (248-561-4434) with any questions.

column16: Graduates from the Class of 2020 are invited to join in a car parade on Thursday, May 28. Graduates will meet and line up in their cars in the AHS parking lot at 6:30 PM. Please feel free to decorate your car and wear your cap and gown. The parade will begin promptly at 7:00 PM and follow the route highlighted on the map provided. Family and friends are encouraged to cheer on the graduates along the parade route. Please adhere to all CDC guidelines pertaining to social distancing and only park and stand on public property. Graduates must also adhere to all CDC guidelines and traffic laws. Graduates will be asked to remain in their cars. Please make sure your car is tastefully decorated. Profanity, vulgar music, and drugs/alcohol will not be tolerated. This is a parent sponsored event. Please contact Jen Donaghy (248-561-7656),Jen Richter (248-396-7427), or Jen Rosasco (248-561-4434) with any questions.

post_text: Graduates from the Class of 2020 are invited to join in a car parade on Thursday, May 28. Graduates will meet and line up in their cars in the AHS parking lot at 6:30 PM. Please feel free to decorate your car and wear your cap and gown. The parade will begin promptly at 7:00 PM and follow the route highlighted on the map provided. Family and friends are encouraged to cheer on the graduates along the parade route. Please adhere to all CDC guidelines pertaining to social distancing and only park and stand on public property. Graduates must also adhere to all CDC guidelines and traffic laws. Graduates will be asked to remain in their cars. Please make sure your car is tastefully decorated. Profanity, vulgar music, and drugs/alcohol will not be tolerated. This is a parent sponsored event. Please contact Jen Donaghy (248-561-7656),Jen Richter (248-396-7427), or Jen Rosasco (248-561-4434) with any questions.

post_text: Graduates from the Class of 2020 are invited to join in a car parade on Thursday, May 28. Graduates will meet and line up in their cars in the AHS parking lot at 6:30 PM. Please feel free to decorate your car and wear your cap and gown. The parade will begin promptly at 7:00 PM and follow the route highlighted on the map provided. Family and friends are encouraged to cheer on the graduates along the parade route. Please adhere to all CDC guidelines pertaining to social distancing and only park and stand on public property. Graduates must also adhere to all CDC guidelines and traffic laws. Graduates will be asked to remain in their cars. Please make sure your car is tastefully decorated. Profanity, vulgar music, and drugs/alcohol will not be tolerated. This is a parent sponsored event. Please contact Jen Donaghy (248-561-7656),Jen Richter (248-396-7427), or Jen Rosasco (248-561-4434) with any questions.

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School senior Rebecca Piepszak! From Mr. Sheldon: "Becky - You are absolutely one of the strongest and most stubborn people I have ever worked with. Your ability to fight for what you think is right is an amazing gift that will serve you well going forward. Your intelligence and drive is something to be very proud of, but your greatest attribute is your ability to empathize with others and make them feel safe and listened to. You have been a wonderful and strong leader for the ATC and I feel so blessed to have been able to see you grow into your big heart." Rebecca will be attending Northern Michigan University in the fall to study Musical Theater. Congratulations again Rebecca!

post_text: HUGE THANK YOU to members of the Rochester Junior Woman's Club who presented us with a $10,000 check to support Avondale Blessings in a Backpack. Each year, the Club selects charities to focus on and have not only contributed financially to help us but have also hosted food drives and helped pack for our weekly distributions. We greatly appreciate their support and partnership now more than ever. Pictured here is Karen Geibel who is the current President and Tanya Armitage-Edgeworth Vice President along with Avondale School District parent and Avondale Blessings in a Backpack Chairperson, Janelle Tischer. Words don't seem to be enough to express how grateful we are for their generosity and efforts to help feed our students but many many heartfelt thanks!

May 12 at 12:59 PM ·

Greetings! We hope everyone is doing well! A Band Booster grandparent was kind enough to sew cute little plush bees (about 9" big) from the old middle school concert uniforms (see attached pictures). We had originally planned to sell them at the Pops Concert, but here we are...We thought people may still be interested, especially graduating seniors since they were the last group to wear the uniforms. We would like to offer them out to the band seniors first as we have limited quantities . They are $25 each. Please contact Juli Drake if interested (248 840 3016). Pickup options include: pickup with cap and gowns, or porch pickup/drop-off. Payment can be made via PayPal (preferred) at bandboostersavondale@gmail.com. Cash or check payments can be arranged (with social distancing :) ). Please let me know if you have any questions and feel free to pass this to any senior (band or not) you like. Take care!

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School senior Nicole Richter! From Mrs. Schupbach: "I was fortunate to have Nicole in multiple classes this year and even when she was not, she would find her way to my room. Even when work was difficult she would never quit. I have no doubt you will be successful in the future with your strong work ethic and dedication to learning. Be confident and never under estimate your ability. Thanks for putting a smile on my face everyday when you would sneak in for help. I will miss you!" Nicole will be attending Western Michigan University to major in Nutrition and Dietetics and minor in Exercise Science. Congratulations again Nicole!

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School senior Thomas Snook! From Mr. Sheldon: "Thomas, I am not even sure how to put into words how proud I am of you. You have been a part of the ATC family for longer than most and your talent in so many areas has been invaluable to all of those that you have worked with. Both onstage where you shared your amazing singing voice, your comedic timing, and surprising Shakespearean Gravitas, and backstage where you led with compassion and care, you have proven what a quality person you are. Thank you and please, take care of your knees!" Thomas will attend Oakland University in the fall to study Chemistry. Congratulations again Thomas!

Ciana will be attending Rochester University to study Theater Management. Congratulations again Ciana!

CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School Top Scholar Preethi Venkatesan! Preethi resides in Rochester Hills with her parents, Elumalai and Selvi Venkatesan. Preethi was a member of the National Honor Society and the Spanish Honor Society. In addition, she was in the Art Club and part of the Green Team, involved in activities designed to build awareness about environmental stewardship. For two years, she participated in Girls Who Code. Preethi is also an accomplished musician.

Foster will be attending Oakland University in the fall to study Mechanical Engineering. Congratulations again Foster!

CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School Top Scholar Preethi Venkatesan! Preethi resides in Rochester Hills with her parents, Elumalai and Selvi Venkatesan. Preethi was a member of the National Honor Society and the Spanish Honor Society. In addition, she was in the Art Club and part of the Green Team, involved in activities designed to build awareness about environmental stewardship. For two years, she participated in Girls Who Code. Preethi is also an accomplished musician.
>>>>>>> master

Preethi plays flute in the Concert Band and the Yellow Jacket Marching Band. She also plays the piano and has earned multiple 1st and 2nd Division ratings for flute and piano solos through the Michigan School Band and Orchestra Association. She has also been a State Qualifier. A member of Avondale Future Problem Solving, Preethi earned semifinalist and finalist designations for her submissions. In the fall, Preethi will be attending Oakland University, pursuing a degree in Engineering. Congratulations again Preethi!

CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School Top Scholar Preethi Venkatesan! Preethi resides in Rochester Hills with her parents, Elumalai and Selvi Venkatesan. Preethi was a member of the National Honor Society and the Spanish Honor Society. In addition, she was in the Art Club and part of the Green Team, involved in activities designed to build awareness about environmental stewardship. For two years, she participated in Girls Who Code. Preethi is also an accomplished musician.

Preethi plays flute in the Concert Band and the Yellow Jacket Marching Band. She also plays the piano and has earned multiple 1st and 2nd Division ratings for flute and piano solos through the Michigan School Band and Orchestra Association. She has also been a State Qualifier. A member of Avondale Future Problem Solving, Preethi earned semifinalist and finalist designations for her submissions. In the fall, Preethi will be attending Oakland University, pursuing a degree in Engineering. Congratulations again Preethi!

CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School Top Scholar Lena Vasylak! Lena is the daughter of Peter Vasylak and Laura Greenwood and she resides in Rochester Hills. She has been on the Principal’s Honor Roll every year throughout middle and high school. She played Varsity tennis in her freshman and sophomore years and Varsity volleyball in her sophomore, junior and senior years.

She served as Team Captain of the volleyball team as a senior and also won the Yellow Jacket Award in volleyball as a senior. Lena played three years of national year-long travel volleyball. She also assisted the Avondale Middle School volleyball coaches with practices and try-outs for four years.
Lena has accepted and signed with Rochester University where she will study Pre-med and play volleyball with both an academic and athletic scholarship. Congratulations again Lena!

CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School Top Scholar Madyson Sowell! Residing in Rochester Hills, Madyson is the daughter of Brian and Keli Sowell. As a member of the National Honor Society, she has volunteered numerous hours within the school district and outside of it. In addition, she has participated in short-term missionary trips, each of the last five years.

Madyson has been on the Principal’s Honor Roll throughout high school as well as earning an NHS Honorable Mention for high academic achievement. She is a four-year Varsity soccer player, awarded the Scholar Athlete Award each year. She is a mentor in the Avondale LINKS Program and a member of the Spectrum yearbook class. Madyson played travel soccer during the school year and in the summer for Troy Soccer Club. In the fall, she will be attending Oakland University, Honors College for Health Sciences, on a Pre-medicine course of study. Congratulations again Madyson!

CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School Top Scholar Alexandra Sokana! Alexandra is the daughter of Lorans Sokana and Stacie McVeigh and she resides in Rochester Hills. She was in the National Honor Society for three years and on the Principal’s Honor Roll throughout high school. She was a mentor in the LINKS program and also volunteered more than 125 hours helping in the community.

Alexandra served as a mentor in the Freshman Transition Class, offering guidance and support to underclassman as they navigated their first year of high school. Alexandra played volleyball for four years, on the Varsity team in her junior and senior years. She was also on the soccer team, on Varsity for her sophomore, junior and senior years and served on the Class Board her senior year. In the fall, Alexandra will attend Michigan State University, Lyman Briggs College to study Human Biology. Her ultimate goal is to become a Pediatrician. Congratulations again Alexandra!

The #birthdaypolice are on patrol! If your child has a birthday during the #stayhomestaysafe order, let us know! We would love to schedule a police car to drive by with lights and sirens blaring, along with a personalized birthday wish (via our public address system, #socialdistance). Let’s work together to make sure our children have something positive on their special day!

To schedule a #birthdaypolice drive-by, contact Officer Brian Miller at bmiller@auburnhills.org. Just let us know the name of your child, age, date and time you want us to visit. Please provide us with a contact phone number as well. Give at least 24 hours notice and due to shift change we won’t be able to come by at 6pm.

CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School Top Scholar Paige Schuster! Paige resides in Rochester Hills and is the daughter of Michael and Tricia Schuster. She was an active member of the National Honor Society for three years and was on the Principal’s Honor Roll throughout middle and high school. In addition, she was a 2019 Michigan Mathematics Prize Competitor, making it to the second round.

Paige was part of the Avondale Theatre Company, contributing to the success of productions including The Fantasticks, Seussical, and Mamma Mia, serving on the props, business and sets crews. In addition, she was working on the business crew for the Curious Incident of the Dog in the Nighttime.

Paige received a merit-based scholarship from Oakland University where she will attend in the fall to study Engineering. Congratulations again Paige!

CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School Top Scholar Dana Holt! Dana resides in Rochester Hills with her parents David and Julie Holt. A member of the Class Board throughout her high school career, Dana was also a member of the Senior Council in her senior year. Taking AP and Honors classes throughout high school, she achieved Principal’s Honor Roll and Scholar Athlete distinction all four years. Dana was part of the first AHS girls’ lacrosse team and was awarded the Purple and Gold Award and the Captain’s Star. CONGRATULATIONS Avondale High School Top Scholar Kelli Crippen! Recently relocating to Shelby Township, Kelli is the daughter of Howard and Kim Crippen. On the Principal’s Honor Roll for four years, Kelli also served on the Executive Board for the Avondale High School Student Council. In addition, Kelli was a committed participant in Leadership Class and Peer Mentoring Class.

A member of the Varsity cheer team for four years, Kelli excelled as a leader and scholar athlete. She served as the Team Captain for two years and was recognized as All-State Academic four times. In addition, she was All-League three consecutive years, in 2017, 2018, and 2019. Kelli will be attending Michigan State University in the fall to pursue a degree in Business. Congratulations again Kelli!
